a cold stone that shines gently in the light. it's green hue permeates the stone so deeply its as if it was frozen in water.
the stone is etched into a serpent shaped into the compact letter S
it's scales create a bumpy hatch texture all on it's body while also gesturing a river flow along its body.
it's said the jade is the body of Mỵ Châu after she was buried

